[src:junit5-java-lib/test-automation] Automation provides many benefits over manual testing.
[src:junit5-java-lib/test-automation] For API testing, tests drive the SUT via its application programming interface (API).
[src:junit5-java-lib/test-automation] Compared to manual testing, automated API testing often can execute a relatively large number of cases in a relatively short time.
[src:junit5-java-lib/test-automation] For GUI testing, tests drive the SUT via its graphical user interface (GUI) by generating events such as keystrokes and mouse clicks.
[src:junit5-java-lib/test-automation] Automated GUI testing can be challenging to develop, but can run much faster than a human could perform the same testing.
[src:junit5-java-lib/test-automation] When automated testing is in place, regression testing can be a relatively quick and easy operation.
[src:junit5-java-lib/test-automation] Instead of a significant outlay of human time and effort, a regression test run could require nothing more than a push of a button and even starting the run can be automated.
[src:junit5-java-lib/test-automation] The following are notable testing techniques categorized as test automation.
[src:junit5-java-lib/test-automation] Continuous testing is the process of executing automated tests as part of the software delivery pipeline to assess the business risk of releasing the SUT.
[src:junit5-java-lib/test-automation] The scope of testing extends from validating bottom-up requirements or user stories to assessing the system requirements associated with overarching business goals.
[src:junit5-java-lib/test-automation] For model-based testing, the SUT is modeled and test cases can be generated from it to support no code test development.
[src:junit5-java-lib/test-automation] Some tools support the encoding of test cases as plain English that can be used on multiple operating systems, browsers, and smart devices.
[src:junit5-java-lib/test-automation] Test-driven development (TDD) inherently includes the generation of automation test code.
[src:junit5-java-lib/test-automation] Unit test code is written while the SUT code is written.
[src:junit5-java-lib/test-automation] When the code is complete, the tests are complete as well.
[src:junit5-java-lib/test-automation] A review of 52 practitioner and 26 academic sources found that five main factors to consider in test automation decision are: system under test (SUT), scope of testing, test toolset, human and organizational topics, cross-cutting factors.
[src:junit5-java-lib/test-automation] The factors most frequently identified were: need for regression testing, economic factors, and maturity of SUT.
[src:junit5-java-lib/test-automation] While the reusability of automated tests is valued by software development companies, this property can also be viewed as a disadvantage as it leads to a plateau effect, where repeatedly executing the same tests stops detecting errors.
[src:junit5-java-lib/test-automation] Testing tools can help automate tasks such as product installation, test data creation, GUI interaction, problem detection (consider parsing or polling agents equipped with test oracles), defect logging, etc., without necessarily automating tests in an end-to-end fashion.
[src:junit5-java-lib/test-automation] To support coded automated testing, the test engineer or software quality assurance person must have software coding ability.
[src:junit5-java-lib/test-automation] Some testing techniques such as table-driven and no-code can lessen or alleviate the need for programming skill.
[src:junit5-java-lib/test-automation] A test automation framework provides a programming environment that integrates test logic, test data, and other resources.
[src:junit5-java-lib/test-automation] The framework provides the basis of test automation and simplifies the automation effort.
[src:junit5-java-lib/test-automation] Using a framework can lower the cost of test development and maintenance.
[src:junit5-java-lib/test-automation] If there is change to any test case then only the test case file needs to be updated and the driver script and startup script will remain the same.
[src:junit5-java-lib/test-automation] A framework is responsible for defining the format in which to express expectations, providing a mechanism to hook into or drive the SUT, executing the tests, and reporting results.
[src:junit5-java-lib/test-automation] A test automation interface is a platform that provides a workspace for incorporating multiple testing tools and frameworks for system/integration testing.
[src:junit5-java-lib/test-automation] A test automation interface may simplify the process of mapping tests to business criteria without coding.
[src:junit5-java-lib/test-automation] A test automation interface may improve the efficiency and flexibility of maintaining tests.
